        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Office blood pressure between 130-179 and 80-110 mmHg for systolic and diastolic blood
             pressure, respectively;

          -  Non-engaged in structured exercise programs in the last 3 months before the beginning
             of this study;

          -  Able to perform the proposed exercises.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Underlying cardiovascular disease in the last 24 months such as acute myocardial
             infarction, angina, stroke or heart failure;

          -  Diseases that reduce life expectancy;

          -  Smokers;

          -  BMI >39.9 kg/mÂ²;

          -  Diabetic proliferative retinopathy.
